MPUMALANGA police are searching for a cattle herder suspected of raping three young boys.The parents of the boys, two aged seven and one of 14 years, opened cases this week, Colonel Bheki Shazi said.&ldquo;The suspect would allegedly first give his victims dagga to smoke and alcohol to drink before sexually abusing each of them. Apparently, these incidents have been taking place in the veld where he watches the cattle.&rdquo;One of the parents said she found signs of abuse while bathing her seven-year-old son. The police&rsquo;s family violence, child protection and sexual offences unit is investigating. &ndash; NEWS24